How to consume JSON data in golang
      Now we're going to see how we can actually consume the json data which is also known as decoding the json data. In many of the application json data will come to you as a api resource or other backend that is being designed and you want to consume this json data. Previously we have consumed the data it was just in the string format, now we want to see that how actually we can consume

// create method to consume data
func DecodeJson() {

	//create JSON data we can request it from the web or create our own data
	//The data that we're receiving from the web is going to be  slice of byte
	jsonDataFromWeb := []byte(`
	{
		"coursename": "ReactJS Bootcamp",
		"Price": 299,
		"website": "abc.com",
		"tags": ["web-dev","js"],
	}
	`)

	//create a variable of type course structs
	//whatever the data is coming up from the web i have created a structure for it and i want to put that into structure
	var lcoCourse course

	//Next we need to be verify that this data is actually in the correct json format using json.Valid()
	checkValid := json.Valid(jsonDataFromWeb)

	if checkValid {
		fmt.Println("JSON was valid")
		//we do an unmarshall, which take 2 parameter, the first one is the data itself and second is the interface (ie)
		//another name for struct, but the problem is that you don't want to pass on just an interface like that because it might give you a copy of that and you want to actually store all of
		//this data so we pass as a reference
		json.Unmarshal(jsonDataFromWeb, &lcoCourse)

		//in order to use or print these interfaces we use %#v
		fmt.Printf("%#v\n", lcoCourse)
	} else {
		fmt.Println("JSON WAS NOT VALID")
	}
}

