Update a record in mongodb in golang
       In update, first we have to provide a filter about which data should we update and the second part of the operation is you need to pass on a flag which is $set  and you pass on the updated information that whatever you want to update

// update 1 record
// create updateOneMovie() which takes movieId as argument
func updateOneMovie(movieId string) {

	/* first we have to convert this movieid into something that mongodb understand, mongodb understand id which internally is in the form of underscore id so we need to fetch that first using primitive.ObjectIDFromHex() which converts string into the object id which is acceptable by the mongodb  during the conversion it's give an id or an error so we use comma ok syntax */
	id, _ := primitive.ObjectIDFromHex(movieId)

	//Now we have to provide a filter, we know everything inside the mongodb is not json technically it is bson and both they look exactly same
	//So we use either bson.M or bson.D, bson.M used for simple filters, updates, inserts where field order doesn’t matter, bson.D used when order matters
	//we use bson.m this where you provide all your query parameters, we know in mongodb it is actually _id  so this is my filter and we use this to fetch an id filter for you 
	filter := bson.M{"_id": id}

	//For update also we use same bson.m, first provide a flag which is a $set, next we want to set further values using bson.m and  if we directly pass on values to bson.m then the values will be always being inserted, but we don't want to insert instead we want to update those values.
	//we have a property watched which is coming up from model and we  turn this flag into true and remember we are not checking that whether this flag is previously true or not but we are always turning this flag into true 
	update := bson.M{"$set": bson.M{"watched": true}}

	// we call updateOne() which takes parameter, first one is context.background, second one is filter based on which it can filter the values and finally value to be updated
	//It returns result or  an error and we have to handle using comma ok syntax
	result, err := collection.UpdateOne(context.Background(), filter, update)
	
	//check for error
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}

	//this result actually gives you a value that how many values are being updated using result.ModifiedCount
	fmt.Println("modified count: ", result.ModifiedCount)
}


Delete one and delete many in mongodb in golang
     Now we want to delete a very specific record and want to delete all the records in the mongodb, both of these operations happens based on the filter. To delete just one record just provide that particular thing, so that it can match just one value and delete that, if you want to
delete all of that just provide an empty set, empty means just everything

// delete 1 movie by passing movieId
func deleteOneMovie(movieId string) {

	//First it convert string movieId to object id with _ that mongodb will understand
	//it returns an id or error so we use comma ok syntax
	id, _ := primitive.ObjectIDFromHex(movieId)

	//We provide a filter based on that it can filter and then we can eventually delete
	//we use bson.M, where we look for an _id that will be matched for with the id that we are giving up
	filter := bson.M{"_id": id}

	//we call deleteOne() whre we provide context.background and requires a filter
	//it returns deletecount or an error so we use comma ok syntax
	deleteCount, err := collection.DeleteOne(context.Background(), filter)

	//check for error
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}

	//return deletecount
	fmt.Println("Movie got delete with delete count: ", deleteCount)
}

// delete all records from mongodb and returns int
func deleteAllMovie() int64 {

	//call DeleteMany() which takes context.background, second one takes a filter by providing bson.D{{}} with an empty parenthesis means everything will be selected  and 3rd arg is nil
	//u can use either bson.M or bson.D 
	//it returns  deleteresult or an error so we use comma ok syntax
	deleteResult, err := collection.DeleteMany(context.Background(), bson.D{{}}, nil)

	//check for error
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}

	//print count from deleteResult
	fmt.Println("NUmber of movies delete: ", deleteResult.DeletedCount)
	return deleteResult.DeletedCount
}


